frameDefinitions: A group of Colonists from a Homeland migrate to and proceed to settle in a New_area.
Generally without overall (translational) motion,  an Agent places a Theme at a location, the Goal, which is profiled.
An Ingestor consumes food or drink (Ingestibles), which entails putting the Ingestibles in the mouth for delivery to the digestive system.
Temporary or permanent Styles and Configurations of Hair, as well as its inherent Nature.
This frame describes a situation in which the Agent puts the Theme into the Ground for the purpose of growing.
frameExamples: In the 7th century BC, Phoenicians <t>colonized</t> the eastern section of Libya.
David <t>placed</t> his briefcase on the floor.
He <t>arranged</t> the elements in the pattern that we now call the periodic table.
On either side her head gleamed coiled <t>braids</t> of dark-gold hair , almost pale copper in the subdued light of the room .
He recently <t>planted</t> some old apple trees. INI
listRoleDefinitions: A group of people who move together to an area outside their <fen>Homeland</fen> for the purpose of settling.
The <fen>Homeland</fen> is where the <fen>Colonists</fen> are originally from.
The <fen>Colonists</fen> move to the <fen>New_area</fen>, inhabiting it and (in the case of nation-states) extending the control of the <fen>Homeland</fen>.
The time at which the colonizing takes place.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person (or other force) that causes the <fen>Theme</fen> to move.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the object that changes location during the Placing.
The role <fen>Goal</fen> is the location where the <fen>Theme</fen> ends up. This role is profiled by words in this frame.
<fen>Time</fen> is when the Placing occurs
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates where the Placing occurs.
The person who causes the <fen>Theme</fen> to be in a particular <fen>Configuration</fen>.
An entity that consists of  parts which can be put into a configuration relative to each other and/or relative to their environment.
A state that holds of the <fen>Theme</fen> or a relation that holds among the constituent parts of the <fen>Theme</fen> as a result of the arranging action.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the arranging takes place.
The <fen>Ingestor</fen> is the person eating or drinking.
The <fen>Ingestibles</fen> are the entities that are being consumed by the <fen>Ingestor</fen>.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
This role is the hair itself
This role is the Possessor of the body part.
Temporary Configurations of hair (eg braid, bun, ponytail).   Something done to the hair merely by movement.
A property of the hair (eg curly, fine, brown).  This acts much like 'Descriptor' in the Observable_bodyparts Frame.  Colors, styles, natural properties are described by this frame element.
The <fen>Agent</fen> plants the <fen>Theme</fen>.
<fen>Theme</fen> is the item planted by the <fen>Agent</fen>.
The <fen>Ground</fen> is the background or context to which the <fen>Agent</fen> pays attention in his agricultural efforts.
When the planting event occurs.
The greater geographic location where the <fen>Agent</fen> plants the <fen>Theme</fen>.
listRoleExamples: <fex>Spain</fex> settled the northern areas of Mexico through the use of missions, civil settlements, and presidios.
Norse invaders in the 900s colonized <fex>the North Midlands</fex> more densely than any other part of England'
<fex>The waiter</fex> placed the food on the table.
The waiter placed <fex>the food</fex> on the table.
The waiter placed the food <fex>on the table</fex>.
Grass , which is sown with clover , provides rich pasture for cattle in summer and the clover is <fex>another plant which</fex> puts nitrogen into the soil .
Smithers had placed the table there <fex>the night before</fex>.
